<Content>Poorodor VIstamar We chose this place for the location and that's about what it was good for. This is a 1960's vintage hotel that has been marginally kept up. They had a nice pool, but as we were there on the weekend, it was crowded with locals drinking and partying to all hours. The signs say that the pool is supposed to close at 10PM, but the very loud music and drinking, etc. continued all night and morning long and the desk would do nothing to stop it (obviously they get the majority of their business from this activity, so the needs of the tourists are not as important). The rooms were run down - the phone did not work, there were bugs, the bathroom floor was always wet because the shower had cracks that allowed it to leak. I'd look for another place if I went back to that area. 
