<Content>OK for a night As a family of four, we spent our first night in Puerto Rico at the Vistamar. The property is located on the side of a mountain with a view of the ocean. Unfortunately, the highway runs between the ocean and the parador and trucks could be heard accelerating or using their airbrakes depending upon their direction on the highway. The coquis chirped merrily all night. We were awakened by roosters in the morning (seems like everyone in the countryside has a rooster).The property was basically pretty clean but a bit dated. 
